The paper discusses feature selection, which is a common problem in machine learning and data analysis. The use of mutual information as a relevance criterion for feature selection suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the limitations of mutual information and proposes modifications to address them, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of feature selection in high-dimensional data also suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
